c-xref - a C/Yacc refactoring tool

Usage:
		c-xref <option>+ <input files>

options:
	-p <project>              - read options from <project> section
	-I <dir>                  - search for includes in <dir>
	-D<macro>[=<body>]        - define macro <macro> with body <body>
	-filescasesensitive       - file names are case sensitive
	-filescaseunsensitive     - file names are case unsensitive
	-csuffixes=<suffixes>     - list of C files suffixes separated by ':' (or ';')
	-xrefrc <file>            - read options from <file> instead of ~/.c-xrefrc
	-o <file>                 - write output to <file>
	-refs <file>              - name of file with cxrefs, or directory if refnum > 1
	-refnum=<n>               - number of cxref files
	-exactpositionresolve     - resolve symbols by def. position
	-mf<n>                    - factor increasing cxMemory
	-errors                   - report all error messages on the console
	                            (by default only fatal errors are shown)
	-warnings                 - also report warning messages on the console
	-infos                    - also report informational & warning messages on the console
	-log=<file>               - log all fatal/error/warnings/informational messages to <file>
	-debug                    - also log debug messages in log
	-trace                    - also log trace & debug messages in log
	-commandlog               - write all commands to /tmp/c-xref-command-log (experimental)
	-compiler=<path>          - path to compiler to use for autodiscovered includes and defines
	-update                   - update existing references database
	-fastupdate               - fast update (modified files only)
	-fullupdate               - full update (all files)
	-version                  - print version information
